#compdef gob
# ============================================================================
#  _gob — gob: stack-based programming language interpreter written in Roc
#         (Isaac Van Doren)
#
#  Source-direct extraction from
#    https://github.com/isaacvando/gob/blob/master/gob.roc
#    https://github.com/roc-lang/basic-cli (Roc basic-cli platform's
#    cli.Arg module — the official Roc stdlib argument parsing module)
#
#  Maintained by Isaac Van Doren (isaacvando/gob).  19 GH stars.  gob
#  is a STACK-BASED programming language (similar to PostScript /
#  Forth / Factor) implemented in Roc.  Provides a minimalist
#  concatenative language for stack-machine experimentation —
#  programs are sequences of operations that push/pop values from
#  an implicit operand stack.  Sister tools: Roc itself (the Roc
#  language compiler, IN CORPUS via _roc), Factor (concatenative
#  language), PostScript (stack-based), Forth (in corpus, R317
#  via _next-arg).
#
#  CLI library taxonomy update: 2nd Roc CLI library — Roc's official
#  basic-cli platform **cli.Arg** module (roc-lang/basic-cli).
#  Roc ecosystem now has 2 documented CLI libraries (R319 smores56/
#  weaver + R401 cli.Arg basic-cli stdlib).
#
#  Roc cli.Arg is the OFFICIAL Roc basic-cli platform's stdlib
#  argument parsing module — built into the basic-cli platform that
#  every Roc command-line application depends on.  Distributed via
#  `cli: platform "https://github.com/roc-lang/basic-cli/releases/...`
#  platform URL in the Roc app header.  Distinct from R319 smores56/
#  weaver (third-party Roc CLI library by Sam Mohr — older, less
#  feature-rich) by being THE OFFICIAL ROC PLATFORM-STDLIB CLI
#  ARGUMENT PARSER.  Used by gob (stack-based language interpreter),
#  bhansconnect/monkey-roc (Monkey language interpreter in Roc),
#  Anton-4/roc-agent (AI agent for Roc programming), growthagent/
#  basic-webserver (extended Roc basic-webserver), ricardo-valero/
#  roc-ngb-emu (Nintendo Game Boy emulator in Roc), Roc's own
#  internal CLI tools (CONTRIBUTING/profiling/exec_bench.roc, build
#  scripts), and ALL modern Roc CLI applications that prefer the
#  PLATFORM-STDLIB approach over the third-party weaver library.
#
#  Roc cli.Arg API:
#    app [main] {
#      cli: platform "https://github.com/roc-lang/basic-cli/releases/...",
#    }
#
