#        description: "A useful tool"
#      }
#      |> Cli.assertValid
#
#  Roc cli.Arg distinctive features:
#    - PLATFORM-STDLIB MODULE — distributed via Roc's official
#      basic-cli platform (`cli: platform "https://github.com/roc-
#      lang/basic-cli/releases/..."` in app header); zero third-party
#      dependency
#    - ROC BACKPASSING-ARROW SYNTAX — uses Roc's distinctive
#      `<-` backpassing arrow operator: `verbose: <- Opt.flag { ... }`
#      means "bind `verbose` to the result of `Opt.flag` and continue
#      with the rest of the record"; this is the Roc language
#      construct (not specific to cli.Arg) for monadic composition
#    - `Cli.build { ... }` — DECLARATIVE RECORD-BASED DSL where each
#      field of the record describes one option/parameter using
#      backpassing arrows
#    - `Opt.flag { short, long, help }` — BOOLEAN flag option
#    - `Opt.str { short, long, help, default: Value "X" }` — REQUIRED
#      string option (errors if not provided)
#    - `Opt.maybeStr { short, long, help }` — OPTIONAL string
#      (returns `Result Str [NoValue]`)
#    - `Opt.u8`/`Opt.u16`/`Opt.u32`/`Opt.u64`/`Opt.u128`/`Opt.i8`/
#      `Opt.i16`/`Opt.i32`/`Opt.i64`/`Opt.i128`/`Opt.dec`/`Opt.f32`/
#      `Opt.f64` — TYPED NUMERIC OPTIONS with auto-coercion (Roc's
#      strict typed numeric system)
#    - `Opt.maybeU32` / `Opt.maybeI64` etc. — OPTIONAL variants
#    - `Param.str { name, help }` — REQUIRED string positional
#    - `Param.maybeStr { name, help }` — OPTIONAL string positional
#    - `Param.strList { name, help, default }` — REPEATED positional
#      (collects all remaining args)
#    - `default: Value V` — DEFAULT VALUE for required options
#    - `default: NoValue` — explicit no-default
#    - `SubCmd.field { name, help, parser }` — NESTED SUBCOMMAND
#      support via SubCmd module
#    - `Cli.finish { name, version, authors, description, help }`
#      — finalize CLI metadata
#    - `Cli.assertValid` — COMPILE-TIME ASSERTION that CLI spec is
#      valid (catches missing fields, conflicts at compile time)
#    - `Cli.parseOrDisplayMessage parser (Arg.list! {})` — main parse
#      entry; on error prints auto-generated help/error to stdout
#      and returns Err for caller to handle
#    - `Arg.list! {}` — Roc TASK-EFFECT-BASED args fetching from the
#      basic-cli platform (`!` is Roc's task-effect suffix for tasks
#      that perform IO)
#    - `Cli.parse parser argv` — LOW-LEVEL parse without auto-display
#    - AUTO-INJECTED `--help`/`-h` and `--version`/`-v` via `Cli.finish`
#    - PROCESS EXIT model — caller handles errors via Task error
#      propagation (`Task.mapErr! \err -> Exit 1 err`); cli.Arg never
#      halts directly
#    - ROC LAMBDA SYNTAX `\arg -> ...` for callbacks
#    - ROC RESULT TYPE for error handling (`Result Str [NoValue]`)
#    - COMPILE-TIME TYPE SAFETY — all option types checked at compile
#      time via Roc's type inference
#  Distinct from R319 Roc smores56/weaver (THIRD-PARTY Roc CLI library
#  by Sam Mohr — older, similar declarative style with `Cli.weave`
#  and Opt/Param modules but DIFFERENT module structure and slightly
#  different API conventions; pre-dates cli.Arg becoming the official
#  basic-cli platform module), R275 Rust clap-derive (Rust struct +
#  macros — CLOSEST conceptual analog with Roc cli.Arg's DECLARATIVE
#  record-based DSL but different language), R346 Scala mainargs
#  (method-parameter binding), R322 Java JCommander (Java annotations),
#  R343 commander.js (JS fluent builder).  Roc cli.Arg's approach:
#  PLATFORM-STDLIB MODULE distributed via basic-cli platform + ROC
#  BACKPASSING-ARROW SYNTAX `verbose: <- Opt.flag { ... }` for
#  monadic composition + `Cli.build { ... }` DECLARATIVE RECORD-
#  BASED DSL + `Opt.X`/`Opt.maybeX`/`Param.X`/`SubCmd.X` typed module
#  organization + RICH NUMERIC TYPES (u8/u16/u32/u64/u128/i8/i16/i32/
#  i64/i128/dec/f32/f64) + `Cli.finish` METADATA FINALIZATION +
#  `Cli.assertValid` COMPILE-TIME VALIDATION + `Cli.parseOrDisplay
#  Message` auto-help-display parse + `Arg.list! {}` TASK-EFFECT-
#  BASED args fetching + AUTO-INJECTED `--help`/`--version` +
#  caller-controlled PROCESS EXIT via Task error propagation +
#  COMPILE-TIME TYPE SAFETY — corpus's **first documented platform-
#  stdlib-with-backpassing-arrow-DSL Roc CLI library**.  Brings
#  cross-language CLI library taxonomy variant count to 140; Roc
#  ecosystem now has 2 documented CLI libraries.
#
#  Surface (verbatim from `gob.roc` `cliParser` definition):
#
#  Options:
#    -p, --pipe                     Read a program from stdin (in
#                                   addition to the file argument)
#    -d, --debug                    Print stack and program state
#                                   during execution (conflicts with
#                                   --step)
#    -s, --step                     Step through execution by pressing
#                                   <enter> (conflicts with --debug;
#                                   if --pipe is specified, may fall
#                                   back to --debug)
#
#  Auto-injected by Roc cli.Arg via Cli.finish:
#    -h, --help                     Show help
#    -v, --version                  Show version
#
#  Positional:
#    PATH                           Path to the gob program to run
#                                   (REQUIRED via Param.str)
#
#  Examples:
#    gob program.gob                # Run program
#    gob -d program.gob             # Run with debug output
#    gob -s program.gob             # Step through execution
#    gob -p program.gob             # Read additional program from
#                                   # stdin and merge with file
#    cat extras.gob | gob -p prog.gob  # Pipe stdin into program
#
#  Dup-skipped neighbors during hunt (in corpus or smaller user base,
#  also Roc cli.Arg users):
#    - monkey-roc (bhansconnect/monkey-roc 7 stars — Monkey language
#      interpreter in Roc; uses cli.Arg with smaller surface)
#    - roc-agent (Anton-4/roc-agent 2 stars — AI agent for Roc
#      programming, early-stage)
#    - basic-webserver (growthagent/basic-webserver 0 stars — extended
#      Roc basic-webserver, library not user-facing CLI)
#    - roc-ngb-emu (ricardo-valero/roc-ngb-emu 1 star — Nintendo Game
#      Boy emulator in Roc, niche)
#    - roc-lang/examples (Roc language example apps, not real binaries)
#    - basic-cli (roc-lang/basic-cli platform itself — the library
#      provides cli.Arg, but the platform isn't a user-facing CLI)
# ============================================================================

_gob() {
  local context state state_descr line
  typeset -A opt_args

  _arguments -s -S \
    '(-p --pipe)'{-p,--pipe}'[read a program from stdin in addition to file]' \
    '(-d --debug)'{-d,--debug}'[print stack and program state during execution]' \
    '(-s --step)'{-s,--step}'[step through execution by pressing enter]' \
    '(-h --help)'{-h,--help}'[show help]' \
    '(-v --version)'{-v,--version}'[show version]' \
    '1:gob program file:_files -g "*.gob"'
}

_gob "$@"
